{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017xgiUm1oD8aZ68FwzdSbyo","type":"tool_result","content":"   200→    totalVolumeLamports: string,\n   201→    totalEarnedLamports: string,\n   202→    pendingLamports: string\n   203→  }\n   204→\n   205→GET  /referral/earnings            — Get detailed per-game earnings log\n   206→  Query: { page?: number, limit?: number }\n   207→  Response: {\n   208→    items: [{\n   209→      roundId: string,\n   210→      gameType: string,\n   211→      refereeWallet: string,\n   212→      wagerLamports: string,\n   213→      earnedLamports: string,\n   214→      createdAt: string\n   215→    }],\n   216→    pagination: { page: number, totalPages: number }\n   217→  }\n   218→\n   219→POST /referral/claim               — Request earnings claim (async via queue)\n   220→  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" }\n   221→\n   222→GET  /referral/claim/:claimId      — Poll claim status\n   223→  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\", txSignature?: string }\n   224→```\n   225→\n   226→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   227→- [ ] All endpoints require JWT authentication <!-- gap: no referral routes registered -->\n   228→- [ ] All endpoints return appropriate error codes (400 for bad input, 404 for not found, 409 for conflict) <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n   229→- [ ] Rate limiting is applied to code generation and claim endpoints <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n   230→- [ ] Monetary values use lamport strings (not floating point) <!-- gap: no API responses to verify -->\n   231→\n   232→### FR-8: Database Schema\n   233→\n   234→New tables for the referral system. All off-chain, no program changes.\n   235→\n   236→```sql\n   237→referral_codes (\n   238→  id            SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   239→  wallet        TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n   240→  code          TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,   -- player-chosen, 3-16 chars [a-z0-9-]\n   241→  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   242→  updated_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   243→)\n   244→\n   245→referral_links (\n   246→  id              SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   247→  referrer_wallet TEXT NOT NULL,\n   248→  referee_wallet  TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,  -- one referrer per player\n   249→  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   250→)\n   251→\n   252→referral_earnings (\n   253→  id                        SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   254→  referrer_wallet           TEXT NOT NULL,\n   255→  referee_wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n   256→  round_id                  TEXT NOT NULL,\n   257→  game_type                 TEXT NOT NULL,\n   258→  wager_lamports            BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   259→  fee_lamports              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   260→  referrer_earned_lamports  BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   261→  referrer_rate_bps         INTEGER NOT NULL,\n   262→  referee_rebate_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   263→  referee_rebate_rate_bps   INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- always 1000 for v1\n   264→  created_at                TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   265→  UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)  -- idempotency: one earning per player per round\n   266→)\n   267→\n   268→referral_claims (\n   269→  id                UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n   270→  wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n   271→  amount_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   272→  status            TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (status IN ('pending','processing','completed','failed')),\n   273→  tx_signature      TEXT,\n   274→  error             TEXT,\n   275→  requested_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   276→  processed_at      TIMESTAMPTZ\n   277→)\n   278→\n   279→-- KOL custom referrer rates (overrides default 1000 bps)\n   280→referral_kol_rates (\n   281→  wallet          TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   282→  rate_bps        INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- e.g., 2000 = 20% of total fee (= 100 bps of wager)\n   283→  set_by          TEXT NOT NULL,     -- admin wallet\n   284→  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   285→  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   286→)\n   287→```\n   288→\n   289→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   290→- [x] All tables created via migration (referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates all 5 tables -->\n   291→- [x] `referral_links.referee_wallet` has UNIQUE constraint (one referrer per player) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:22 — referee_wallet TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n   292→- [x] `referral_codes.code` has UNIQUE constraint <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:12 — code TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n   293→- [x] Appropriate indexes on wallet columns and `referral_earnings.round_id` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — 6 indexes covering all wallet lookups and round_id -->\n   294→- [x] `referral_earnings` has unique idempotency guard (`UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)`) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:43-44 — CONSTRAINT uq_referral_earnings_referee_round -->\n   295→- [x] `referral_claims.status` constrained to `pending|processing|completed|failed` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:67-68 — CHECK constraint chk_referral_claims_status -->\n   296→\n   297→### FR-9: Frontend — Routes, Pages, and Components\n   298→\n   299→All frontend changes live in `apps/platform/`. Follows existing patterns: React Router routes in `App.tsx`, NavLink in `Sidebar.tsx`, feature code in `features/referral/`, API wrappers in `lib/referral-api.ts`.\n   300→\n   301→#### 9a. New Route: `/r/:code` — Referral Link Handler\n   302→\n   303→A lightweight route that captures the referral code from the URL, persists it, and redirects to the home page (or wherever the player was headed).\n   304→\n   305→**Flow:**\n   306→1. Player visits `taunt.bet/r/my-code`\n   307→2. Route component reads `:code` via `useParams()`\n   308→3. Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n   309→4. Redirects to `/` via `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />`\n   310→5. On next authentication (in `SessionContext` or a dedicated `useReferralApply` hook), if `referral_code` exists in localStorage and user has no referrer → calls `POST /referral/apply` → clears localStorage on success\n   311→\n   312→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   313→- [ ] Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n   314→- [ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required) <!-- gap: no localStorage referral code logic -->\n   315→- [ ] Redirect to `/` happens immediately after capture <!-- gap: no route handler -->\n   316→- [ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n   317→- [ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked) <!-- gap: no apply logic -->\n   318→- [ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error <!-- gap: no error handling -->\n   319→\n   320→#### 9b. Sidebar Navigation — Referrals Link\n   321→\n   322→New nav item in the \"Player\" section of `Sidebar.tsx`, between \"Quests\" and the \"Platform\" section.\n   323→\n   324→```tsx\n   325→<NavLink to=\"/referrals\" className={({ isActive }) => `nv-item ${isActive ? \"active\" : \"\"}`}\n   326→  style={{ \"--nc\": \"var(--color-green)\" } as React.CSSProperties}>\n   327→  <div className=\"nv-ico\">\n   328→    {/* share/link icon */}\n   329→  </div>\n   330→  <span className=\"nv-lbl\">Referrals</span>\n   331→</NavLink>\n   332→```\n   333→\n   334→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   335→- [ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section <!-- gap: not in Sidebar.tsx -->\n   336→- [ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   337→- [ ] Icon is a share/link-style SVG consistent with sidebar icon style <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   338→- [ ] Navigates to `/referrals` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   339→\n   340→#### 9c. Referral Page (`/referrals`)\n   341→\n   342→Main referral hub page at route `/referrals`. Requires wallet connection + authentication. Shows different states based on whether the player has generated a code yet.\n   343→\n   344→**Layout — top to bottom:**\n   345→\n   346→1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   347→   - If no code yet: input field to choose a custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button → calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }` → shows link\n   348→   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   349→   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   350→   - \"Change code\" link → inline edit field to set a new custom code → calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }`\n   351→\n   352→2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   353→   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   354→   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   355→   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports → SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   356→   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n   357→\n   358→3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   359→   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   360→   - \"Claim\" button — enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   361→   - Claim flow: button → loading state → calls `POST /referral/claim` → success toast with tx link → refresh stats\n   362→   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n   363→\n   364→4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   365→   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   366→   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   367→   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   368→   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n   369→\n   370→**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n   371→\n   372→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   373→- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n   374→- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n   375→- [ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n   376→- [ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n   377→- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n   378→- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n   379→- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n   380→- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n   381→- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n   382→- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n   383→\n   384→#### 9d. Profile Settings — Referral Code Input\n   385→\n   386→In the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n   387→\n   388→**Layout:**\n   389→- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n   390→- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n   391→- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n   392→- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n   393→\n   394→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   395→- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n   396→- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   397→- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   398→- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   399→- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8cdd94d4-4d50-4151-8136-428429db5806","uuid":"00011777-4bf2-479e-b2e2-1ce51a2d7041","timestamp":"2026-03-25T15:25:18.702Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"    totalVolumeLamports: string,\n    totalEarnedLamports: string,\n    pendingLamports: string\n  }\n\nGET  /referral/earnings            — Get detailed per-game earnings log\n  Query: { page?: number, limit?: number }\n  Response: {\n    items: [{\n      roundId: string,\n      gameType: string,\n      refereeWallet: string,\n      wagerLamports: string,\n      earnedLamports: string,\n      createdAt: string\n    }],\n    pagination: { page: number, totalPages: number }\n  }\n\nPOST /referral/claim               — Request earnings claim (async via queue)\n  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" }\n\nGET  /referral/claim/:claimId      — Poll claim status\n  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\", txSignature?: string }\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All endpoints require JWT authentication <!-- gap: no referral routes registered -->\n- [ ] All endpoints return appropriate error codes (400 for bad input, 404 for not found, 409 for conflict) <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n- [ ] Rate limiting is applied to code generation and claim endpoints <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n- [ ] Monetary values use lamport strings (not floating point) <!-- gap: no API responses to verify -->\n\n### FR-8: Database Schema\n\nNew tables for the referral system. All off-chain, no program changes.\n\n```sql\nreferral_codes (\n  id            SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  wallet        TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  code          TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,   -- player-chosen, 3-16 chars [a-z0-9-]\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n\nreferral_links (\n  id              SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  referrer_wallet TEXT NOT NULL,\n  referee_wallet  TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,  -- one referrer per player\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n\nreferral_earnings (\n  id                        SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  referrer_wallet           TEXT NOT NULL,\n  referee_wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n  round_id                  TEXT NOT NULL,\n  game_type                 TEXT NOT NULL,\n  wager_lamports            BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  fee_lamports              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  referrer_earned_lamports  BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  referrer_rate_bps         INTEGER NOT NULL,\n  referee_rebate_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  referee_rebate_rate_bps   INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- always 1000 for v1\n  created_at                TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)  -- idempotency: one earning per player per round\n)\n\nreferral_claims (\n  id                UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n  wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n  amount_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  status            TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (status IN ('pending','processing','completed','failed')),\n  tx_signature      TEXT,\n  error             TEXT,\n  requested_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  processed_at      TIMESTAMPTZ\n)\n\n-- KOL custom referrer rates (overrides default 1000 bps)\nreferral_kol_rates (\n  wallet          TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  rate_bps        INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- e.g., 2000 = 20% of total fee (= 100 bps of wager)\n  set_by          TEXT NOT NULL,     -- admin wallet\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] All tables created via migration (referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates all 5 tables -->\n- [x] `referral_links.referee_wallet` has UNIQUE constraint (one referrer per player) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:22 — referee_wallet TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n- [x] `referral_codes.code` has UNIQUE constraint <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:12 — code TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n- [x] Appropriate indexes on wallet columns and `referral_earnings.round_id` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — 6 indexes covering all wallet lookups and round_id -->\n- [x] `referral_earnings` has unique idempotency guard (`UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)`) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:43-44 — CONSTRAINT uq_referral_earnings_referee_round -->\n- [x] `referral_claims.status` constrained to `pending|processing|completed|failed` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:67-68 — CHECK constraint chk_referral_claims_status -->\n\n### FR-9: Frontend — Routes, Pages, and Components\n\nAll frontend changes live in `apps/platform/`. Follows existing patterns: React Router routes in `App.tsx`, NavLink in `Sidebar.tsx`, feature code in `features/referral/`, API wrappers in `lib/referral-api.ts`.\n\n#### 9a. New Route: `/r/:code` — Referral Link Handler\n\nA lightweight route that captures the referral code from the URL, persists it, and redirects to the home page (or wherever the player was headed).\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Player visits `taunt.bet/r/my-code`\n2. Route component reads `:code` via `useParams()`\n3. Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n4. Redirects to `/` via `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />`\n5. On next authentication (in `SessionContext` or a dedicated `useReferralApply` hook), if `referral_code` exists in localStorage and user has no referrer → calls `POST /referral/apply` → clears localStorage on success\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n- [ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required) <!-- gap: no localStorage referral code logic -->\n- [ ] Redirect to `/` happens immediately after capture <!-- gap: no route handler -->\n- [ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked) <!-- gap: no apply logic -->\n- [ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error <!-- gap: no error handling -->\n\n#### 9b. Sidebar Navigation — Referrals Link\n\nNew nav item in the \"Player\" section of `Sidebar.tsx`, between \"Quests\" and the \"Platform\" section.\n\n```tsx\n<NavLink to=\"/referrals\" className={({ isActive }) => `nv-item ${isActive ? \"active\" : \"\"}`}\n  style={{ \"--nc\": \"var(--color-green)\" } as React.CSSProperties}>\n  <div className=\"nv-ico\">\n    {/* share/link icon */}\n  </div>\n  <span className=\"nv-lbl\">Referrals</span>\n</NavLink>\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section <!-- gap: not in Sidebar.tsx -->\n- [ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Icon is a share/link-style SVG consistent with sidebar icon style <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Navigates to `/referrals` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9c. Referral Page (`/referrals`)\n\nMain referral hub page at route `/referrals`. Requires wallet connection + authentication. Shows different states based on whether the player has generated a code yet.\n\n**Layout — top to bottom:**\n\n1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   - If no code yet: input field to choose a custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button → calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }` → shows link\n   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   - \"Change code\" link → inline edit field to set a new custom code → calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }`\n\n2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports → SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n\n3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   - \"Claim\" button — enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   - Claim flow: button → loading state → calls `POST /referral/claim` → success toast with tx link → refresh stats\n   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n\n4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n\n**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n- [ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n\n#### 9d. Profile Settings — Referral Code Input\n\nIn the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n\n**Layout:**\n- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->","numLines":200,"startLine":200,"totalLines":715}}}
