{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EPRqbvBKpEmnVp3aLh7fVU","type":"tool_result","content":"   400→\n   401→#### 9e. API Client — `lib/referral-api.ts`\n   402→\n   403→Thin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n   404→\n   405→```typescript\n   406→const BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n   407→\n   408→export async function setReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   409→export async function getReferralCode(token: string);\n   410→export async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   411→export async function getReferralStats(token: string);\n   412→export async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\n   413→export async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\n   414→export async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n   415→```\n   416→\n   417→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   418→- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented (`setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`) with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n   419→- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   420→- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   421→- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   422→\n   423→#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook — `useReferralApply`\n   424→\n   425→A hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n   426→\n   427→```typescript\n   428→// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\n   429→export function useReferralApply() {\n   430→  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n   431→  const { address } = useWallet();\n   432→\n   433→  useEffect(() => {\n   434→    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n   435→    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n   436→    if (!stored) return;\n   437→    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n   438→    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n   439→      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n   440→      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n   441→  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n   442→}\n   443→```\n   444→\n   445→Mount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n   446→\n   447→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   448→- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n   449→- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   450→- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   451→- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) — retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   452→- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   453→- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   454→\n   455→### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n   456→\n   457→The referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n   458→\n   459→**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n   460→1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n   461→2. If referrer exists → calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports × referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports × fee_bps / 10000)\n   462→3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n   463→4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n   464→\n   465→**Referrer rate lookup:**\n   466→1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n   467→2. If found → use KOL rate\n   468→3. If not → use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   469→\n   470→**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n   471→\n   472→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   473→- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n   474→- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n   475→- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n   476→- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n   477→- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n   478→- [ ] No additional RPC calls — purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n   479→- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->\n   480→\n   481→---\n   482→\n   483→### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n   484→\n   485→Referral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n   486→\n   487→**Event types (v1):**\n   488→- `referral.claim_requested` — emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n   489→\n   490→Note: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings — only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n   491→\n   492→**Payload contract:**\n   493→\n   494→`referral.claim_requested`\n   495→```json\n   496→{\n   497→  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",\n   498→  \"wallet\": \"string\",\n   499→  \"amountLamports\": \"string\",\n   500→  \"requestedAt\": \"ISO-8601 timestamp\"\n   501→}\n   502→```\n   503→\n   504→**Idempotency key:** `referral:claim:{claimId}`\n   505→\n   506→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   507→- [ ] `referral.claim_requested` event emitted with the payload above when a claim is created <!-- gap: no claim endpoint to emit events -->\n   508→- [ ] Handler validates payload shape; malformed payloads are dead-lettered <!-- gap: no handler registered -->\n   509→- [ ] Handler performs idempotency check: if claim already completed/failed, no-op <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   510→- [ ] Handler re-verifies available balance before transfer (prevents overpay on concurrent claims) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   511→- [ ] Handler sends SOL from treasury to wallet, records tx_signature in `referral_claims` <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   512→- [ ] Re-processing the same event is a safe no-op (no duplicate SOL transfers) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   513→\n   514→---\n   515→\n   516→## Design Decisions (v1)\n   517→\n   518→### Why immutable referrer linkage\n   519→\n   520→- Prevents referral hijacking and user confusion.\n   521→- Simplifies all downstream aggregation and payout logic.\n   522→- Keeps fraud analysis tractable (single parent per user graph).\n   523→\n   524→### Why async claims (not synchronous transfer API)\n   525→\n   526→- Wallet RPC operations are the slowest and least reliable part of the flow.\n   527→- Async queue gives retries/backoff and keeps user request latency low.\n   528→- Prevents backend API threads from being tied up by treasury transfer delays.\n   529→\n   530→### Why persist economic inputs in `referral_earnings`\n   531→\n   532→- Store `fee_lamports` + `referrer_rate_bps` with each earning row to preserve historical correctness.\n   533→- Future rate changes do not retroactively affect past earnings or audits.\n   534→- Makes dispute/debug workflows deterministic from DB data alone.\n   535→\n   536→---\n   537→\n   538→## Success Criteria\n   539→\n   540→- Players can set a custom code, share it, and apply referral codes without friction\n   541→- Referral earnings are calculated correctly and match expected economics (1000 bps of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   542→- Claim flow delivers SOL to the player's wallet reliably\n   543→- System handles concurrent operations without double-crediting or double-claiming\n   544→- No on-chain program changes required — entirely off-chain for v1\n   545→- Settlement path latency is not measurably affected by referral logic\n   546→- Rewards and claims are processed async via event queue (spec 301) without blocking game loops\n   547→\n   548→---\n   549→\n   550→## Dependencies\n   551→\n   552→- Existing JWT authentication system (spec 007)\n   553→- **Async event queue (spec 301)** — referee rewards and claim payouts are processed via the queue\n   554→- Backend settlement worker (must be extended with referral earnings hook + event emission)\n   555→- Treasury wallet with sufficient SOL for claim payouts\n   556→- Frontend routing for `/r/{CODE}` deep links\n   557→- Environment variables for default referral rate (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS=1000`) and claim threshold (`REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS=10000000`)\n   558→\n   559→## Assumptions\n   560→\n   561→- Fee structure is 500 bps (5%) flat fee to single treasury (PlatformConfig on-chain)\n   562→- Treasury wallet is funded and managed outside this spec\n   563→- Referral system launches alongside or after existing games (coinflip, lord-of-rngs)\n   564→- No on-chain enforcement of referral economics needed for v1\n   565→- Postgres `SKIP LOCKED` is available (Postgres 9.5+ — already met)\n   566→\n   567→---\n   568→\n   569→## Validation Plan\n   570→\n   571→| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   572→|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   573→| 1 | Code generation works | API test: generate code, verify format and DB entry | Test output |\n   574→| 2 | Custom codes validated | API test: valid/invalid custom codes | Test output |\n   575→| 3 | Referral linking via URL | E2E: visit /r/CODE, authenticate, verify link created | Test output + DB check |\n   576→| 4 | Manual code entry works | API test: apply code via endpoint | Test output |\n   577→| 5 | Self-referral blocked | API test: apply own code, expect 400 | Test output |\n   578→| 6 | Immutable referrer | API test: apply second code after first, expect 409 | Test output |\n   579→| 7 | Earnings calculated at settlement | Integration test: settle game for referred player, check referral_earnings | Test output + DB check |\n   580→| 8 | KOL custom rate applied | Integration test: set KOL rate, settle game, verify different earning | Test output |\n   581→| 9 | Stats endpoint accurate | API test: create referrals + earnings, verify stats math | Test output |\n   582→| 10 | Claim delivers SOL | Integration test: claim flow, verify tx on-chain | Tx signature |\n   583→| 11 | Concurrent claim prevention | Load test: parallel claims, verify only one succeeds | Test output |\n   584→| 12 | Referee bonus reward granted | Integration test: apply code + complete game, verify reward trigger fired via queue | Test output + DB check |\n   585→| 21 | Async claim completes via queue | Integration test: POST claim → poll status → verify completed with tx sig | Test output + Tx sig |\n   586→| 22 | Welcome reward fires on code apply | Integration test: apply code → verify `referral.code_applied` event processed | Test output + DB check |\n   587→| 23 | Queue infrastructure works (spec 301) | See spec 301 validation plan | Per spec 301 |\n   588→| 13 | `/r/:code` captures + redirects | E2E: visit referral URL, check localStorage, verify redirect to `/` | Browser test |\n   589→| 14 | Auto-apply on auth | E2E: store code in localStorage, connect wallet, verify referral link created + localStorage cleared | Browser test |\n   590→| 15 | Referral page renders all sections | Visual test: code card, stats, claim, earnings table in correct layout | Screenshot |\n   591→| 16 | Copy link works | E2E: click copy button, verify clipboard content matches referral URL | Browser test |\n   592→| 17 | Sidebar nav item present | Visual test: \"Referrals\" link visible in Player section, active state works | Screenshot |\n   593→| 18 | Profile settings code input | E2E: enter code in profile settings, verify referral linked | Browser test |\n   594→| 19 | Unauthenticated state | Visual test: `/referrals` without wallet shows connect prompt | Screenshot |\n   595→| 20 | Claim button states | E2E: disabled when below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with tx link | Browser test |\n   596→\n   597→---\n   598→\n   599→## Completion Signal"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8cdd94d4-4d50-4151-8136-428429db5806","uuid":"92b53374-4206-4717-881d-180ab1f9b572","timestamp":"2026-03-25T15:25:19.706Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"\n#### 9e. API Client — `lib/referral-api.ts`\n\nThin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n\n```typescript\nconst BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n\nexport async function setReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralCode(token: string);\nexport async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralStats(token: string);\nexport async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\nexport async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\nexport async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented (`setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`) with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook — `useReferralApply`\n\nA hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n\n```typescript\n// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\nexport function useReferralApply() {\n  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n  const { address } = useWallet();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n    if (!stored) return;\n    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n}\n```\n\nMount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) — retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n\n### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n\nThe referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n\n**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n2. If referrer exists → calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports × referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports × fee_bps / 10000)\n3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n\n**Referrer rate lookup:**\n1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n2. If found → use KOL rate\n3. If not → use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n\n**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n- [ ] No additional RPC calls — purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->\n\n---\n\n### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n\nReferral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n\n**Event types (v1):**\n- `referral.claim_requested` — emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n\nNote: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings — only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n\n**Payload contract:**\n\n`referral.claim_requested`\n```json\n{\n  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"wallet\": \"string\",\n  \"amountLamports\": \"string\",\n  \"requestedAt\": \"ISO-8601 timestamp\"\n}\n```\n\n**Idempotency key:** `referral:claim:{claimId}`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `referral.claim_requested` event emitted with the payload above when a claim is created <!-- gap: no claim endpoint to emit events -->\n- [ ] Handler validates payload shape; malformed payloads are dead-lettered <!-- gap: no handler registered -->\n- [ ] Handler performs idempotency check: if claim already completed/failed, no-op <!-- gap: no handler -->\n- [ ] Handler re-verifies available balance before transfer (prevents overpay on concurrent claims) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n- [ ] Handler sends SOL from treasury to wallet, records tx_signature in `referral_claims` <!-- gap: no handler -->\n- [ ] Re-processing the same event is a safe no-op (no duplicate SOL transfers) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n\n---\n\n## Design Decisions (v1)\n\n### Why immutable referrer linkage\n\n- Prevents referral hijacking and user confusion.\n- Simplifies all downstream aggregation and payout logic.\n- Keeps fraud analysis tractable (single parent per user graph).\n\n### Why async claims (not synchronous transfer API)\n\n- Wallet RPC operations are the slowest and least reliable part of the flow.\n- Async queue gives retries/backoff and keeps user request latency low.\n- Prevents backend API threads from being tied up by treasury transfer delays.\n\n### Why persist economic inputs in `referral_earnings`\n\n- Store `fee_lamports` + `referrer_rate_bps` with each earning row to preserve historical correctness.\n- Future rate changes do not retroactively affect past earnings or audits.\n- Makes dispute/debug workflows deterministic from DB data alone.\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Players can set a custom code, share it, and apply referral codes without friction\n- Referral earnings are calculated correctly and match expected economics (1000 bps of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n- Claim flow delivers SOL to the player's wallet reliably\n- System handles concurrent operations without double-crediting or double-claiming\n- No on-chain program changes required — entirely off-chain for v1\n- Settlement path latency is not measurably affected by referral logic\n- Rewards and claims are processed async via event queue (spec 301) without blocking game loops\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Existing JWT authentication system (spec 007)\n- **Async event queue (spec 301)** — referee rewards and claim payouts are processed via the queue\n- Backend settlement worker (must be extended with referral earnings hook + event emission)\n- Treasury wallet with sufficient SOL for claim payouts\n- Frontend routing for `/r/{CODE}` deep links\n- Environment variables for default referral rate (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS=1000`) and claim threshold (`REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS=10000000`)\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- Fee structure is 500 bps (5%) flat fee to single treasury (PlatformConfig on-chain)\n- Treasury wallet is funded and managed outside this spec\n- Referral system launches alongside or after existing games (coinflip, lord-of-rngs)\n- No on-chain enforcement of referral economics needed for v1\n- Postgres `SKIP LOCKED` is available (Postgres 9.5+ — already met)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Code generation works | API test: generate code, verify format and DB entry | Test output |\n| 2 | Custom codes validated | API test: valid/invalid custom codes | Test output |\n| 3 | Referral linking via URL | E2E: visit /r/CODE, authenticate, verify link created | Test output + DB check |\n| 4 | Manual code entry works | API test: apply code via endpoint | Test output |\n| 5 | Self-referral blocked | API test: apply own code, expect 400 | Test output |\n| 6 | Immutable referrer | API test: apply second code after first, expect 409 | Test output |\n| 7 | Earnings calculated at settlement | Integration test: settle game for referred player, check referral_earnings | Test output + DB check |\n| 8 | KOL custom rate applied | Integration test: set KOL rate, settle game, verify different earning | Test output |\n| 9 | Stats endpoint accurate | API test: create referrals + earnings, verify stats math | Test output |\n| 10 | Claim delivers SOL | Integration test: claim flow, verify tx on-chain | Tx signature |\n| 11 | Concurrent claim prevention | Load test: parallel claims, verify only one succeeds | Test output |\n| 12 | Referee bonus reward granted | Integration test: apply code + complete game, verify reward trigger fired via queue | Test output + DB check |\n| 21 | Async claim completes via queue | Integration test: POST claim → poll status → verify completed with tx sig | Test output + Tx sig |\n| 22 | Welcome reward fires on code apply | Integration test: apply code → verify `referral.code_applied` event processed | Test output + DB check |\n| 23 | Queue infrastructure works (spec 301) | See spec 301 validation plan | Per spec 301 |\n| 13 | `/r/:code` captures + redirects | E2E: visit referral URL, check localStorage, verify redirect to `/` | Browser test |\n| 14 | Auto-apply on auth | E2E: store code in localStorage, connect wallet, verify referral link created + localStorage cleared | Browser test |\n| 15 | Referral page renders all sections | Visual test: code card, stats, claim, earnings table in correct layout | Screenshot |\n| 16 | Copy link works | E2E: click copy button, verify clipboard content matches referral URL | Browser test |\n| 17 | Sidebar nav item present | Visual test: \"Referrals\" link visible in Player section, active state works | Screenshot |\n| 18 | Profile settings code input | E2E: enter code in profile settings, verify referral linked | Browser test |\n| 19 | Unauthenticated state | Visual test: `/referrals` without wallet shows connect prompt | Screenshot |\n| 20 | Claim button states | E2E: disabled when below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with tx link | Browser test |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal","numLines":200,"startLine":400,"totalLines":715}}}
