{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TqKq4hEuLPuZeVLvEgqnyk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Implementation History — 300-referral-system\n     2→\n     3→Iteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\n     4→attempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\n     5→of every iteration to understand prior context.\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## Iteration 1 — 2026-03-24T21:27:27Z — OK\n    10→\n    11→**Item**: [backend] Database migration `011_referral.sql`\n    12→**Status**: Done\n    13→**Changes**:\n    14→- Created `services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` with all 5 referral tables:\n    15→  - `referral_codes` — one code per wallet (UNIQUE on wallet + code)\n    16→  - `referral_links` — immutable referrer binding (UNIQUE on referee_wallet)\n    17→  - `referral_earnings` — per-game earnings with idempotency guard (UNIQUE on referee_wallet + round_id)\n    18→  - `referral_claims` — async payout tracking with status CHECK constraint (pending/processing/completed/failed)\n    19→  - `referral_kol_rates` — KOL custom rates (wallet PK)\n    20→- Indexes: referrer/referee wallet lookups on earnings, round_id, claims by wallet+date, partial index on pending/processing claims, referrer_wallet on links\n    21→- Follows existing migration patterns (IF NOT EXISTS, TIMESTAMPTZ, BIGINT for lamports, no foreign keys)\n    22→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18 tasks)\n    23→**Note**: Agent falsely claimed DONE after this single item. Loop accepted it (no guard).\n    24→\n    25→## Gap Analysis — 2026-03-24T21:41:16Z\n    26→- **Result**: Gap analysis report generated\n    27→- **Report**: gap-analysis.md\n    28→- **Log**: gap-analysis.log\n    29→\n    30→## Iteration 2 — 2026-03-25T08:54:27Z — FALSE DONE (rejected retroactively)\n    31→- **Agent claimed DONE** but only the migration was complete. Checklist was refined between runs.\n    32→- **Log