{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Nn6czXFFEPQi9zcJJAj3ke","type":"tool_result","content":"   120→ * Errors are logged but never bubble — referral recording must not fail settlement.\n   121→ * The UNIQUE(referee_wallet, round_id) constraint provides idempotency on retries.\n   122→ */\n   123→async function recordReferralEarnings(\n   124→  db: Db,\n   125→  params: {\n   126→    roundId: string;\n   127→    gameType: string;\n   128→    feeBps: number;\n   129→    referralDefaultRateBps: number;\n   130→    players: Array<{ wallet: string; wagerLamports: number }>;\n   131→  },\n   132→): Promise<void> {\n   133→  const { roundId, gameType, feeBps, referralDefaultRateBps, players } = params;\n   134→\n   135→  // Deduplicate players (Lord of RNGs can have multiple entries per player)\n   136→  const playerWagers = new Map<string, number>();\n   137→  for (const p of players) {\n   138→    playerWagers.set(p.wallet, (playerWagers.get(p.wallet) ?? 0) + p.wagerLamports);\n   139→  }\n   140→\n   141→  for (const [wallet, wagerLamports] of playerWagers) {\n   142→    try {\n   143→      const link = await db.getReferralLinkByReferee(wallet);\n   144→      if (!link) continue;\n   145→\n   146→      const referrerWallet = link.referrer_wallet;\n   147→      const referrerRateBps = await db.getReferrerRate(\n   148→        referrerWallet,\n   149→        referralDefaultRateBps,\n   150→      );\n   151→\n   152→      const feeLamports = Math.floor((wagerLamports * feeBps) / 10_000);\n   153→      const referrerEarnedLamports = Math.floor(\n   154→        (feeLamports * referrerRateBps) / 10_000,\n   155→      );\n   156→      const refereeRebateLamports = Math.floor((feeLamports * 1000) / 10_000);\n   157→\n   158→      await db.insertReferralEarning({\n   159→        referrerWallet,\n   160→        refereeWallet: wallet,\n   161→        roundId,\n   162→        gameType,\n   163→        wagerLamports,\n   164→        feeLamports,\n   165→        referrerEarnedLamports,\n   166→        referrerRateBps,\n   167→        refereeRebateLamports,\n   168→        refereeRebateRateBps: 1000, // fixed 10% for v1\n   169→      });\n   170→\n   171→      logger.info(\"referral earning recorded\", {\n   172→        roundId,\n   173→        gameType,\n   174→        referrer: referrerWallet,\n   175→        referee: wallet,\n   176→        referrerEarnedLamports,\n   177→        refereeRebateLamports,\n   178→      });\n   179→    } catch (err: unknown) {\n   180→      const msg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n   181→      if (msg.includes(\"duplicate key\") || msg.includes(\"unique constraint\")) {\n   182→        logger.info(\"referral earning already recorded (idempotent skip)\", {\n   183→          roundId,\n   184→          wallet,\n   185→        });\n   186→      } else {\n   187→        logger.error(\"failed to record referral earning\", {\n   188→          roundId,\n   189→          wallet,\n   190→          error: msg,\n   191→        });\n   192→      }\n   193→    }\n   194→  }\n   195→}\n   196→\n   197→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   198→// Core settle function\n   199→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8cdd94d4-4d50-4151-8136-428429db5806","uuid":"9c335d75-de1e-4638-bc43-b43c35cfe896","timestamp":"2026-03-25T15:28:40.602Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts","content":" * Errors are logged but never bubble — referral recording must not fail settlement.\n * The UNIQUE(referee_wallet, round_id) constraint provides idempotency on retries.\n */\nasync function recordReferralEarnings(\n  db: Db,\n  params: {\n    roundId: string;\n    gameType: string;\n    feeBps: number;\n    referralDefaultRateBps: number;\n    players: Array<{ wallet: string; wagerLamports: number }>;\n  },\n): Promise<void> {\n  const { roundId, gameType, feeBps, referralDefaultRateBps, players } = params;\n\n  // Deduplicate players (Lord of RNGs can have multiple entries per player)\n  const playerWagers = new Map<string, number>();\n  for (const p of players) {\n    playerWagers.set(p.wallet, (playerWagers.get(p.wallet) ?? 0) + p.wagerLamports);\n  }\n\n  for (const [wallet, wagerLamports] of playerWagers) {\n    try {\n      const link = await db.getReferralLinkByReferee(wallet);\n      if (!link) continue;\n\n      const referrerWallet = link.referrer_wallet;\n      const referrerRateBps = await db.getReferrerRate(\n        referrerWallet,\n        referralDefaultRateBps,\n      );\n\n      const feeLamports = Math.floor((wagerLamports * feeBps) / 10_000);\n      const referrerEarnedLamports = Math.floor(\n        (feeLamports * referrerRateBps) / 10_000,\n      );\n      const refereeRebateLamports = Math.floor((feeLamports * 1000) / 10_000);\n\n      await db.insertReferralEarning({\n        referrerWallet,\n        refereeWallet: wallet,\n        roundId,\n        gameType,\n        wagerLamports,\n        feeLamports,\n        referrerEarnedLamports,\n        referrerRateBps,\n        refereeRebateLamports,\n        refereeRebateRateBps: 1000, // fixed 10% for v1\n      });\n\n      logger.info(\"referral earning recorded\", {\n        roundId,\n        gameType,\n        referrer: referrerWallet,\n        referee: wallet,\n        referrerEarnedLamports,\n        refereeRebateLamports,\n      });\n    } catch (err: unknown) {\n      const msg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n      if (msg.includes(\"duplicate key\") || msg.includes(\"unique constraint\")) {\n        logger.info(\"referral earning already recorded (idempotent skip)\", {\n          roundId,\n          wallet,\n        });\n      } else {\n        logger.error(\"failed to record referral earning\", {\n          roundId,\n          wallet,\n          error: msg,\n        });\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Core settle function\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------","numLines":80,"startLine":120,"totalLines":919}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RUBjkfPooEze71u3GYG2Yg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the implementation. Let me now compile the gap analysis. Let me identify the key findings:\n\n**Rate limiting for referral routes:** Not specifically applied. The rate limiting middleware is only on `/auth/*` and `/fairness/*` routes. The `/referral/*` routes only have JWT auth but no rate limiting. This is a GAP for FR-7 criterion about rate limiting.\n\n**Toast notification on auto-apply:** The hook has a TODO comment and uses `console.warn` instead of an actual toast. This is a GAP for FR-9f.\n\n**Concurrent claims prevention (DB-level locking):** The claim route snapshots the balance, then creates a claim in a transaction. \n\nThe issue is that `getPendingBalance` runs outside the transaction, so two concurrent requests could both read the same balance and create duplicate claims. The handler re-verifies afterward as a safety net, but the spec requires DB-level locking on the balance snapshot itself—that's missing at the route level. This is a partial gap: the handler provides a second line of defense, but the explicit DB-level locking isn't implemented.\n\nNow I'm going through the functional requirements systematically. For FR-1 on referral code generation, I'm checking each criterion: the API endpoint is authenticated, the validation regex and uniqueness constraints are in place, the database schema enforces one active code per player via the UNIQUE constraint and upsert logic, and I need to verify the persistence requirement.\n\nFor FR-2 on referral linking, I'm verifying that the localStorage capture works on the referral URL, the application logic connects stored codes to authenticated players, the manual entry flow exists through the settings page, and the database prevents reassigning referrers with its uniqueness constraint.\n\nFor FR-3 on referee rebates, I'm checking that rebate amounts are calculated and recorded when games settle, and confirming the rebate is fixed at 1000 basis points of the fee amount. sum referrer_earned + sum referee_rebate - claims), so both earnings types combine into one claimable amount. Moving on to the referrer fee share requirements, I can see the referral earnings are calculated when a game settles through the settlement transaction logic, with a configurable default rate of 1000 basis points. KOL wallets can have custom rates stored in the database, and earnings are recorded per-game with the necessary fields tracked.\n\nFor the earnings dashboard, the referral page displays all the key summary stats including referred count, active players, volume, and total earned, with a separate card showing the pending claimable balance. There's also a detailed earnings log that's paginated and shows individual game entries through an API endpoint. The stats are updating in near real-time... , amount_lamports, status, timestamps, tx_signature (on success)` — SATISFIED: 011_referral.sql referral_claims table\n5. `[ ] Concurrent claims from the same wallet are prevented (DB-level locking on balance snapshot)` — GAP: The claim route snapshots balance before the transaction without DB-level locking (FOR UPDATE). The handler re-verifies, which provides some protection, but the spec requires locking at the route level. Looking at this more carefully though: when a claim is created, it's inserted as `pending` and `getPendingBalance` subtracts all pending/processing/completed claims from the total. So if two concurrent requests hit the endpoint, they'd both see the same balance before either claim is recorded, meaning both could claim the full amount — that's the race condition the locking would prevent.\n\nHowever, the handler does re-verify by checking if the pending balance (earnings minus all claims) exceeds the requested amount, so if both claims are pending, the second one would fail when it sees negative pending balance. The system prevents double-claiming at the handler level, but allows duplicate claim rows to be created at the API level, which is a moderate gap from the spec's requirement.\n\n6. `[ ] Zero-balance claims are rejected with a clear error message` — SATISFIED: referral.\n\nts:351-362 ZERO_BALANCE check\n\n7. `[ ] Minimum claim threshold is enforced (e.g., 0.01 SOL) to avoid dust transactions` — SATISFIED: referral.ts:364-375 BELOW_THRESHOLD check with config.referralMinClaimLamports\n\n8. `[x] Failed transfers are retried by the queue (up to max_attempts) with exponential backoff` — SATISFIED: queue/worker.ts implements exponential backoff\n\n**FR-7: API Contract (4 criteria)**\n\n1. `[ ] All endpoints require JWT authentication` — SATISFIED: index.ts:95-98 JWT middleware with requireAllMethods: true\n\n2. `[ ] All endpoints return appropriate error codes (400 for bad input, 404 for not found, 409 for conflict)` — SATISFIED: referral.ts uses 400, 404, 409 as appropriate\n\n3. `[ ] Rate limiting is applied to code generation and claim endpoints` — GAP: Rate limiting middleware is only applied to `/auth/*` and `/fairness/*` routes. No rate limiting on `/referral/*` routes (index.ts:94-99 only has JWT, no rate limit).\n\n4. `[ ] Monetary values use lamport strings (not floating point)` — SATISFIED: All API responses use string lamports (referral.ts response objects use lamport strings)\n\n**FR-8: Database Schema (6 criteria)** — All SATISFIED (already marked [x] in spec)\n\n**FR-9a: Route /r/:code (6 criteria)**\n\n1. `[ ] Route /r/:code registered in App.tsx` — SATISFIED: App.tsx:387\n\n2. `[ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required)` — SATISFIED: App.tsx:460\n\n3. `[ ] Redirect to / happens immediately after storing the code` — checking the implementation details for this redirect behavior\n\n4. `[ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API` — SATISFIED: useReferralApply.ts:55\n\n5. `[ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked)` — SATISFIED: useReferralApply.ts:57, 74\n\n6. `[ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error` — GAP: useReferralApply.ts:58 has TODO for toast, uses console.warn instead\n\n**FR-9b: Sidebar Navigation (4 criteria)**\n\n1. `[ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section` — SATISFIED: Sidebar.tsx:162-171\n\n2. `[ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items` — SATISFIED: Uses same className pattern as other NavLinks\n\n3. Checking icon implementation...\n\n4. `[ ] Navigates to /referrals` — SATISFIED: to=\"/referrals\"\n\n**FR-9c: Referral Page (10 criteria)**\n\n1. `[ ] Route /referrals registered in App.tsx, renders ReferralPage` — SATISFIED: App.tsx:383\n\n2. `[ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description` — SATISFIED: ReferralPage.tsx:12-25\n\n3. `[ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, [a-z0-9-]) and shows errors inline` — SATISFIED: ReferralLinkCard.tsx:9 regex\n\n4. `[ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL` — SATISFIED: ReferralLinkCard.tsx display mode\n\n5. Checking copy button functionality...\n\n6. `[ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton` — SATISFIED: ReferralStatsCard.tsx\n\n7. `[ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim` — SATISFIED: ReferralClaimCard.tsx\n\n8. Looking at the claim success state — the spec calls for a toast with transaction link, but the component shows an inline success banner instead. This still satisfies the requirement since it displays the explorer link, just in a different format than a traditional toast notification.\n\n9. `[ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns` — SATISFIED: ReferralEarningsTable.tsx\n\n10. `[ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section` — SATISFIED: ReferralEarningsTable.tsx\n\nNow checking the Profile Settings requirements — the referral code input section is properly integrated into the settings tab, the POST endpoint is wired up correctly, and when a user is already referred, their referrer's wallet displays as read-only.\n\nValidation errors render inline rather than just in the console, and attempting self-referral triggers an appropriate error message.\n\nMoving to the API client layer — all the referral functions are implemented with JWT Bearer authentication, response parsing follows the established pattern from the auth module, error messages are user-friendly rather than raw HTTP statuses, and everything's properly typed with request and response interfaces.\n\nNow examining the referral apply hook...\n\nit reads the referral code from localStorage after authentication succeeds, automatically calls the apply endpoint, and clears storage on success or permanent failures like invalid codes. For transient failures like network errors, it preserves the code so the next auth attempt can retry. There's a gap though — the success toast notification still has a TODO comment and is using console.warn instead of the proper toast component, and I need to verify it's mounted in the main App component.\n\nNow looking at the backend settlement integration, the worker correctly checks for a referrer after each game settles, calculates earnings as basis points of the total fee rather than the wager amount, applies custom KOL rates when available with a fallback to the default, and ensures the earnings row gets inserted atomically within the same database transaction as the settlement itself.\n\nHowever, there's a gap in the event emission — the settlement path inserts the earnings row directly into the database but doesn't emit a `referral.game_settled` event to the async queue for downstream processing like referee rewards and notifications. The event type exists in the codebase but isn't being used during settlement, even though the spec explicitly requires it. There's a tension in the spec itself—FR-11 says no async handler is needed for earnings since they're written synchronously, but FR-10 criterion 5 expects a referral event emitted to an async queue. The `REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED` event type exists but is never actually emitted, so I'm marking this as a moderate gap since the core functionality works but the event emission doesn't. For the remaining criteria, the RPC calls check passes since it's purely DB operations, though I can't verify the latency requirement through static analysis alone.\n\nMoving to FR-11 now, the claim_requested event is properly emitted with the right payload structure. For the handler validation piece, I'm seeing that the payload gets destructured in the handler, which would throw if malformed, but the spec specifically calls for dead-lettering malformed payloads rather than just retrying them—that's a gap in the current implementation.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2999,"cache_read_input_tokens":82380,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2999},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8cdd94d4-4d50-4151-8136-428429db5806","uuid":"8e62db2e-dd79-4b68-89e5-243b316f83ef"}
