ies available balance before transfer | GAP | No handler |","-| 11e | Handler sends SOL from treasury, records tx_signature | GAP | No handler |","-| 11f | Re-processing same event is safe no-op | GAP | No handler |","+| 11a | `referral.claim_requested` emitted with correct payload | SATISFIED | `referral.ts:393-402` emitEvent with `{ claimId, wallet, amountLamports, requestedAt }` |","+| 11b | Handler validates payload; malformed payloads dead-lettered | **GAP** | `referral-claim.ts:34-38` validates and throws on missing fields. However, the throw causes the queue worker to retry (exponential backoff until max_attempts). Spec says \"dead-lettered\" (no retry for malformed). Wastes retries on permanently broken payloads. |","+| 11c | Idempotency: completed/failed claims are no-op | SATISFIED | `referral-claim.ts:47-59` returns early for completed or failed status |","+| 11d | Re-verifies balance before transfer | SATISFIED | `referral-claim.ts:65-81` checks `pending >= amount`, fails claim if insufficient |","+| 11e | Sends SOL and records tx_signature | SATISFIED | `referral-claim.ts:83-109` SystemProgram.transfer; records via `updateClaimStatus` |","+| 11f | Re-processing same event is safe no-op | SATISFIED | Idempotency check at handler entry; completed claims skipped |"," "," ---"," "]},{"oldStart":293,"oldLines":26,"newStart":319,"newLines":15,"lines":[" "," | # | FR | Criterion | Severity | Category | Blocked By | Next Step |"," |---|-----|-----------|----------|----------|------------|-----------|","-| 1 | FR-1 | 1a: Set code via API | critical | backend | DB methods done, needs route | Implement `POST /referral/code` in `routes/referral.ts` |","-| 2 | FR-1 | 1b: Code validation (3-16, [a-z0-9-]) | critical | backend | Route needed | Add validation in route handler |","-| 3 | FR-2 | 2a: `/r/:code` stores code in localStorage | moderate | frontend | API endpoints | Implement `/r/:code` route in App.tsx |","-| 4 | FR-2 | 2b: Auto-apply on auth | moderate | frontend | API endpoints | Implement `useReferralApply` hook |","-| 5 | FR-2 | 2c: Manual code entry via API | critical | backend+frontend | Route needed | `POST /referral/apply` + profile UI |","-| 6 | FR-2 | 2e: Self-referral rejection | critical | backend | Route needed | API-level wallet check |","-| 7 | FR-3 | 3a-3e: All referee rebate criteria | critical | backend | Settlement hook | Settlement integration + balance aggregation |","-| 8 | FR-4 | 4a: Earnings calculated at settlement | critical | backend | Settlement hook | `settle-tx.ts` referral hook |","-| 9 | FR-4 | 4b: Default rate from config | moderate | backend | — | Add `REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS` to config.ts |","-| 10 | FR-5 | 5a-5d: All dashboard/stats criteria | moderate | frontend+backend | API endpoints | `GET /referral/stats` + `GET /referral/earnings` + frontend page |","-| 11 | FR-6 | 6a-6c, 6e-6g: Claim flow | critical | backend | DB methods | `POST /referral/claim` + claim handler |","-| 12 | FR-7 | 7a-7d: All API contract criteria | critical | backend | Routes | Implement all 7 endpoints in `routes/referral.ts` |","-| 13 | FR-9 | 9a-9f: All frontend criteria (48 sub-criteria) | moderate | frontend | API endpoints | Full frontend implementation |","-| 14 | FR-10 | 10a-10g: Settlement integration | critical | backend | DB methods for earnings/rates | Hook into `settle-tx.ts` |","-| 15 | FR-11 | 11a-11f: Claim handler idempotency | critical | backend | Claim endpoint | Register handler in queue registry |","-| 16 | — | Backend referral route tests | moderate | test | Routes | Write alongside route implementation |","-| 17 | — | Backend settlement integration test | moderate | test | Settlement hook | Write alongside settlement hook |","-| 18 | — | Local E2E tests | low | test | Frontend + backend | After full stack implementation |","-| 19 | — | Visual baselines | low | test | Frontend | After referral page implemented |","+| 1 | FR-6 | Concurrent claims DB-level locking on balance snapshot | moderate | backend | — | Add `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE` or similar locking in the claim route's balance snapshot query, or wrap the snapshot + claim creation in a serializable transaction |","+| 2 | FR-7 | Rate limiting on code generation and claim endpoints | moderate | backend | — | Apply `createRateLimitMiddleware` to `/referral/*` routes in `index.ts` (same pattern as `/auth/*` and `/fairness/*`) |","+| 3 | FR-9a | Invalid/expired codes show toast notification | low | frontend | Toast system | `useReferralApply.ts:58` TODO — implement toast when toast system is available, or use a lightweight inline notification |","+| 4 | FR-9f | Success toast on referral auto-apply | low | frontend | Toast system | Same as #3 — `useReferralApply.ts:58` uses `console.warn` |","+| 5 | FR-10 | `referral.game_settled` event not emitted in settlement | low | backend | — | Add `emitEvent(tx, EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED, ...)` in `recordReferralEarnings` within the settlement transaction. Event type already defined. |","+| 6 | FR-11 | Malformed payloads dead-lettered (not retried) | low | backend | — | Catch validation errors in claim handler and return without throwing (no-op), or add dead-letter classification to the queue worker |"," ","+Severity: **critical** (blocks launch) / **moderate** (degrades UX or safety) / **low** (polish)","+"," ---"," "," ## Deferred Items"]},{"oldStart":321,"oldLines":51,"newStart":336,"newLines":20,"lines":[" |------|-------------|-------------|---------------|--------|"," | — | — | — | — | — |"," ","-No items are deferred — all gaps are within scope of this spec.","+No items are explicitly deferred. All gaps are implementation oversights, not intentional deferrals."," "," ---"," ","-## Verdicts Summary","+## Recommendations"," ","-| Verdict | Count |","-|---------|-------|","-| SATISFIED | 17 |","-| DEFERRED | 0 |","-| GAP | 73 |","-| **Total** | **90** |","+1. **Rate limiting (moderate, quick fix):** Add `createRateLimitMiddleware` to `/referral/*` routes in `index.ts`. This is a one-line addition following the existing pattern for `/auth/*` and `/fairness/*`. Priority: high — unprotected POST endpoints are an abuse vector."," ","-### Satisfied Items (17)","+2. **Concurrent claim locking (moderate):** The current defense-in-depth (handler re-verification) prevents actual double-payout, but allows creation of duplicate `pending` claim rows. Options:","+   - Wrap balance snapshot + claim insert in a single `sql.begin` with `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE` on the pending balance","+   - Add a partial unique index on `referral_claims(wallet)` WHERE `status IN ('pending','processing')` to prevent multiple active claims"," ","-| # | FR | Criterion | Evidence |","-|---|-----|-----------|----------|","-| 1 | FR-1 | 1c: One active code per player | `011_referral.sql` UNIQUE(wallet) + `db.ts:680` upsertReferralCode |","-| 2 | FR-1 | 1d: Code persisted in table | `011_referral.sql` + `db.ts:657` insertReferralCode |","-| 3 | FR-2 | 2d: Cannot change referrer | `011_referral.sql:22` UNIQUE on referee_wallet + `db.ts:694` insertReferralLink throws on dup |","-| 4 | FR-2 | 2f: Link stored with timestamp | `011_referral.sql:17-22` + `db.ts:694-701` insertReferralLink |","-| 5 | FR-4 | 4c: KOL custom rates | `011_referral.sql:78-84` referral_kol_rates table |","-| 6 | FR-4 | 4d: Earnings per-game with fields | `011_referral.sql:28-44` referral_earnings table |","-| 7 | FR-4 | 4e: No cap or expiry | No TTL/cap in schema |","-| 8 | FR-6 | 6d: Claim record with fields | `011_referral.sql:56-68` referral_claims table |","-| 9 | FR-6 | 6h: Retry with backoff | `queue/worker.ts:193-202` exponential backoff |","-| 10 | FR-8 | 8a: All tables via migration | `011_referral.sql` |","-| 11 | FR-8 | 8b: referee_wallet UNIQUE | `011_referral.sql:22` |","-| 12 | FR-8 | 8c: code UNIQUE | `011_referral.sql:12` |","-| 13 | FR-8 | 8d: Indexes | `011_referral.sql` 6 indexes |","-| 14 | FR-8 | 8e: Idempotency guard | `011_referral.sql:42-43` |","-| 15 | FR-8 | 8f: Status CHECK constraint | `011_referral.sql:67-68` |","-| 16 | FR-2 | 2d: DB-level duplicate link prevention | `011_referral.sql:22` + `db.ts:694` insertReferralLink |","-| 17 | FR-2 | 2f: Link stored with db.ts method | `db.ts:694-701` insertReferralLink |","+3. **Toast notifications (low, blocked):** The `useReferralApply` hook has a TODO for toast integration. Both FR-9a and FR-9f reference toast notifications. This requires either: (a) a platform-wide toast/notification system, or (b) a lightweight inline notification. Could be deferred to a platform UX enhancement spec."," ","-**Note:** FR-8 (Database Schema) accounts for 6 SATISFIED. Queue infrastructure (FR-6 6h) adds 1. DB-level constraints and methods across FR-1 (2), FR-2 (2+2 with new link methods), FR-4 (3), FR-6 (1) account for the rest. Total is 17 after adding the 2 new link method-backed criteria (2d and 2f now have both schema AND db.ts method evidence).","+4. **`referral.game_settled` event emission (low):** The event type exists but is never emitted. This is low priority since earnings are written synchronously and no downstream handler is registered. Would matter when notifications or analytics consumers are added. Simple fix: one `emitEvent` call in `recordReferralEarnings`."," ","----","-","-## Recommendations","-","-1. **Next iteration: DB client methods for earnings + claims + stats + rates** — these 8 missing methods (`insertReferralEarning`, `getPendingBalance`, `getReferralEarnings`, `getReferralStats`, `insertReferralClaim`, `getReferralClaim`, `updateClaimStatus`, `getReferrerRate`) are the foundation for all remaining backend work","-2. **Then: Config env vars** (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS`, `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS`) in `config.ts` — needed by routes and settlement hook","-3. **Then: API routes (`routes/referral.ts`)** — 7 endpoints enabling frontend work. Register in `index.ts` at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware","-4. **Then: Settlement integration** — core earning mechanism in `settle-tx.ts`, wrapped in `sql.transaction()` with atomicity guarantee","-5. **Then: Claim handler** — register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue, with idempotency, balance re-verification, and SOL transfer","-6. **Frontend can be parallelized** once API endpoints exist — start with API client, then routes/hooks, then page components","-7. **Tests should be written alongside each component** — not batched at the end","+5. **Dead-letter classification (low):** The queue worker treats all handler errors as retryable. Adding a `DeadLetterError` or similar classification would let handlers signal \"this will never succeed, don't retry.\" Low urgency since malformed payloads are rare in practice (events are emitted by the same backend)."]}],"originalFile":"# Gap Analysis: 300-referral-system — Referral System\n\n- **Date**: 2026-03-25\n- **Spec status**: Ready\n- **Previous analysis**: 2026-03-25 (post-iteration-3)\n\n## Changes Since Last Analysis\n\n| Item | Previous | Current | Notes |\n|------|----------|---------|-------|\n| DB client methods (link CRUD) | GAP | SATISFIED | Iteration 4: `insertReferralLink`, `getReferralLinkByReferee`, `getReferralLinksByReferrer` added to `db.ts:694-716` |\n| `ReferralLink` type | GAP | SATISFIED | Interface added to `db.ts:138-143` |\n\nAll other items remain unchanged — no new API routes, settlement hooks, frontend components, or claim handlers were added since the previous analysis.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Inventory\n\n### On-Chain Instructions\n\nNo on-chain changes required for this spec (v1 is entirely off-chain).\n\n| Instruction | Program | File | Line |\n|------------|---------|------|------|\n| N/A | — | — | — |\n\n### Backend — Database Migration\n\n| Table | File | Line | Status |\n|-------|------|------|--------|\n| `referral_codes` | `services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` | 8-14 | DONE |\n| `referral_links` | `services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` | 17-22 | DONE |\n| `referral_earnings` | `services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` | 28-44 | DONE |\n| `referral_claims` | `services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` | 56-68 | DONE |\n| `referral_kol_rates` | `services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` | 78-84 | DONE |\n| Indexes (6) | `services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` | 24-75 | DONE |\n\n### Backend — DB Client Methods\n\n| Method | File | Line (interface) | Line (impl) | Status |\n|--------|------|------------------|-------------|--------|\n| `ReferralCode` interface | `services/backend/src/db.ts` | 130-136 | — | DONE |\n| `ReferralLink` interface | `services/backend/src/db.ts` | 138-143 | — | DONE |\n| `insertReferralCode` | `services/backend/src/db.ts` | 283 | 657-664 | DONE |\n| `getReferralCodeByWallet` | `services/backend/src/db.ts` | 286 | 666-671 | DONE |\n| `getReferralCodeByCode` | `services/backend/src/db.ts` | 289 | 673-678 | DONE |\n| `upsertReferralCode` | `services/backend/src/db.ts` | 292 | 680-690 | DONE |\n| `insertReferralLink` | `services/backend/src/db.ts` | 299 | 694-701 | DONE |\n| `getReferralLinkByReferee` | `services/backend/src/db.ts` | 302 | 703-708 | DONE |\n| `getReferralLinksByReferrer` | `services/backend/src/db.ts` | 305 | 710-716 | DONE |\n| `insertReferralEarning` | — | — | — | GAP |\n| `getPendingBalance` | — | — | — | GAP |\n| `getReferralEarnings` | — | — | — | GAP |\n| `getReferralStats` | — | — | — | GAP |\n| `insertReferralClaim` | — | — | — | GAP |\n| `getReferralClaim` | — | — | — | GAP |\n| `updateClaimStatus` | — | — | — | GAP |\n| `getReferrerRate` | — | — | — | GAP |\n\n### Backend — Queue Infrastructure\n\n| Component | File | Line | Status |\n|-----------|------|------|--------|\n| Event types (3) | `services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts` | 9-11 | DONE |\n| Event emitter | `services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts` | 18-34 | DONE |\n| Handler registry | `services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts` | 16-30 | DONE |\n| Worker (polling + backoff) | `services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts` | 41-202 | DONE |\n| Worker startup | `services/backend/src/index.ts` | 172-175 | DONE |\n| Queue unit tests | `services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue.test.ts` | — | DONE |\n| Queue integration tests | `services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts` | — | DONE |\n\n### Backend — Not Implemented\n\n| Component | Expected File | Status |\n|-----------|---------------|--------|\n| API routes (7 endpoints) | `services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts` | GAP |\n| Route registration | `services/backend/src/index.ts` | GAP |\n| Settlement hook | `services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` | GAP |\n| Claim queue handler | `services/backend/src/queue/` (handler) | GAP |\n| Config env vars (REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS, REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS) | `services/backend/src/config.ts` | GAP |\n| DB methods: earnings, claims, stats, rates | `services/backend/src/db.ts` | GAP |\n\n### Frontend Components\n\n| Component | File | Line | Status |\n|-----------|------|------|--------|\n| — | — | — | All GAP |\n\n### Frontend — Not Implemented\n\n| Component | Expected File | Status |\n|-----------|---------------|--------|\n| API client (7 functions) | `apps/platform/src/lib/referral-api.ts` | GAP |\n| Route `/r/:code` | `apps/platform/src/App.tsx` | GAP |\n| Route `/referrals` | `apps/platform/src/App.tsx` | GAP |\n| `useReferralApply` hook | `apps/platform/src/features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts` | GAP |\n| Sidebar nav item | `apps/platform/src/components/Sidebar.tsx` | GAP |\n| `ReferralPage` component | `apps/platform/src/features/referral/` | GAP |\n| Profile referral section | `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/` | GAP |\n\n### Tests\n\n| Test | Type | File | Status |\n|------|------|------|--------|\n| Queue unit tests | unit | `services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue.test.ts` | DONE |\n| Queue integration tests | integration | `services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts` | DONE |\n| Backend referral route tests | unit | — | GAP |\n| Backend settlement integration test | integration | — | GAP |\n| Local E2E tests | e2e | — | GAP |\n| Visual baselines (`/referrals`, sidebar) | visual | — | GAP |\n| Devnet E2E | e2e | — | N/A (no VRF/oracle) |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Audit\n\n### FR-1: Referral Code Generation\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 1a | Authenticated player can set a referral code via API | GAP | `routes/referral.ts` does not exist — no HTTP endpoint for code setting |\n| 1b | Code is always player-chosen, 3-16 chars, validated against `[a-z0-9-]`, unique | GAP | No route-level validation logic; DB unique constraint exists but API layer missing |\n| 1c | Each player has exactly one active code (setting new replaces old) | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql`: `referral_codes.wallet` UNIQUE; `db.ts:680` `upsertReferralCode` ON CONFLICT replaces |\n| 1d | Code is persisted in `referral_codes` table | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql` creates table; `db.ts:657` `insertReferralCode` implements INSERT |\n\n### FR-2: Referral Linking\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 2a | Visiting `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}` stores the code (localStorage) until auth | GAP | No `/r/:code` route in `App.tsx` |\n| 2b | On authentication, stored/submitted code creates the link | GAP | No `useReferralApply` hook |\n| 2c | Player can manually enter a referral code via API (settings page) | GAP | No `POST /referral/apply` endpoint or profile UI |\n| 2d | Attempting to change an existing referrer returns an error | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql:22`: `referee_wallet TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE` prevents second link at DB level; `db.ts:694` `insertReferralLink` will throw on duplicate |\n| 2e | Self-referral (referrer wallet = referee wallet) is rejected | GAP | No API-level validation implemented |\n| 2f | Referral link is stored in `referral_links` table with `created_at` timestamp | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql:17-22` creates table with `created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()`; `db.ts:694-701` `insertReferralLink` inserts rows |\n\n### FR-3: Referee Fee Rebate\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 3a | After a referred player's game settles, a rebate row is recorded in `referral_earnings.referee_rebate_lamports` | GAP | No settlement hook in `settle-tx.ts` — grep returns zero matches for \"referral\" in worker directory |\n| 3b | Rebate is exactly 1000 bps of fee_lamports (fixed, not configurable) | GAP | No calculation logic implemented |\n| 3c | Rebate accrues to the referee's claimable balance (same claim flow as referrer earnings) | GAP | No claim flow or balance calculation |\n| 3d | Benefit is communicated in the UI on the referral page and at code entry | GAP | No frontend referral page |\n| 3e | A player who is both a referrer AND a referee sees a single combined pending balance | GAP | No balance aggregation logic |\n\n### FR-4: Referrer Fee Share\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 4a | When a referred player's game settles, the referrer's earning is calculated and stored | GAP | No settlement hook |\n| 4b | Default referrer rate is 1000 bps of the total fee (configurable via environment/config) | GAP | No config env var `REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS` — grep in `config.ts` returns zero matches for \"referral\" |\n| 4c | KOL wallets can have a custom rate set by admin | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql:78-84`: `referral_kol_rates` table with `rate_bps`, `set_by`, timestamps |\n| 4d | Earnings are recorded per-game in `referral_earnings` with required fields | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql:28-44`: table has all specified columns |\n| 4e | Referrer earnings accrue indefinitely with no cap or expiry | SATISFIED | No TTL or cap constraint in `011_referral.sql` |\n\n### FR-5: Earnings Dashboard & Stats\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 5a | Referral page shows summary stats | GAP | No frontend referral page |\n| 5b | Detailed earnings log is available, paginated | GAP | No `GET /referral/earnings` endpoint |\n| 5c | Stats update in near-real-time (within settlement latency) | GAP | No stats endpoint or settlement hook |\n| 5d | Page is accessible from main navigation or profile section | GAP | No sidebar nav item — grep for \"referral\" in `Sidebar.tsx` returns zero matches |\n\n### FR-6: Claim Flow\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 6a | Player can claim their full pending referral balance | GAP | No claim endpoint or handler |\n| 6b | Claim request returns immediately (202 Accepted) with a claim ID | GAP | No `POST /referral/claim` endpoint |\n| 6c | Queue worker executes the SOL transfer from treasury to player wallet | GAP | No claim handler registered — handler registry has no referral handler implementations |\n| 6d | Claim is recorded with: wallet, amount_lamports, status, timestamps, tx_signature | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql:56-68`: `referral_claims` table has all specified columns |\n| 6e | Concurrent claims from the same wallet are prevented (DB-level locking) | GAP | No claim logic to use locking |\n| 6f | Zero-balance claims are rejected with a clear error message | GAP | No claim endpoint |\n| 6g | Minimum claim threshold is enforced | GAP | No threshold config or validation — `config.ts` has no `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS` |\n| 6h | Failed transfers are retried by the queue with exponential backoff | SATISFIED | `queue/worker.ts:193-202` implements exponential backoff (5s→30s→300s) for all event types |\n\n### FR-7: API Contract\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 7a | All endpoints require JWT authentication | GAP | No referral routes registered — `index.ts` has no `/referral` mount |\n| 7b | All endpoints return appropriate error codes (400, 404, 409) | GAP | No referral routes |\n| 7c | Rate limiting is applied to code generation and claim endpoints | GAP | No referral routes |\n| 7d | Monetary values use lamport strings (not floating point) | GAP | No API responses to verify |\n\n### FR-8: Database Schema\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 8a | All tables created via migration | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql`: 5 tables created (`referral_codes`, `referral_links`, `referral_earnings`, `referral_claims`, `referral_kol_rates`) |\n| 8b | `referral_links.referee_wallet` has UNIQUE constraint | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql:22`: `referee_wallet TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE` |\n| 8c | `referral_codes.code` has UNIQUE constraint | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql:12`: `code TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE` |\n| 8d | Appropriate indexes on wallet columns and `referral_earnings.round_id` | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql`: 6 indexes covering referrer/referee wallet lookups, round_id, claims by wallet, pending/processing claims |\n| 8e | `referral_earnings` has unique idempotency guard | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql:42-43`: `CONSTRAINT uq_referral_earnings_referee_round UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)` |\n| 8f | `referral_claims.status` constrained to pending/processing/completed/failed | SATISFIED | `011_referral.sql:67-68`: `CONSTRAINT chk_referral_claims_status CHECK (status IN ('pending','processing','completed','failed'))` |\n\n### FR-9: Frontend — Routes, Pages, and Components\n\n#### 9a: `/r/:code` Route\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 9a-1 | Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx` | GAP | Not in App.tsx routes (lines 366-382 — no referral routes) |\n| 9a-2 | Code stored in localStorage on visit | GAP | No localStorage referral code logic anywhere in frontend |\n| 9a-3 | Redirect to `/` happens immediately | GAP | No route handler |\n| 9a-4 | On successful auth, stored code is applied via API | GAP | No `useReferralApply` hook |\n| 9a-5 | localStorage is cleared after successful apply | GAP | No apply logic |\n| 9a-6 | Invalid/expired codes show toast, not blocking error | GAP | No error handling |\n\n#### 9b: Sidebar Navigation\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 9b-1 | \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section | GAP | Not in Sidebar.tsx — current Player section has Profile, Loot Crates, Quests only |\n| 9b-2 | Active state styling matches existing nav items | GAP | Not implemented |\n| 9b-3 | Icon is a share/link-style SVG | GAP | Not implemented |\n| 9b-4 | Navigates to `/referrals` | GAP | Not implemented |\n\n#### 9c: Referral Page\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 9c-1 | Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx` | GAP | Not in App.tsx routes |\n| 9c-2 | Unauthenticated users see connect-wallet prompt | GAP | No ReferralPage component |\n| 9c-3 | Code input validates and shows errors inline | GAP | No component |\n| 9c-4 | Setting code displays referral URL | GAP | No component |\n| 9c-5 | Copy button copies URL with visual feedback | GAP | No component |\n| 9c-6 | Stats summary loads with loading skeleton | GAP | No component |\n| 9c-7 | Claim button disabled below threshold, loading during claim | GAP | No component |\n| 9c-8 | Successful claim shows toast with tx link | GAP | No component |\n| 9c-9 | Earnings table loads paginated data | GAP | No component |\n| 9c-10 | Empty states have meaningful messages | GAP | No component |\n\n#### 9d: Profile Settings\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 9d-1 | Referral code input section in profile settings | GAP | Not in profile components — ProfileSettings.tsx has no referral section |\n| 9d-2 | Input calls `POST /referral/apply` | GAP | Not implemented |\n| 9d-3 | If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only) | GAP | Not implemented |\n| 9d-4 | Validation errors display inline | GAP | Not implemented |\n| 9d-5 | Self-referral attempt shows clear error | GAP | Not implemented |\n\n#### 9e: API Client\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 9e-1 | All 7 API functions with JWT auth | GAP | `lib/referral-api.ts` does not exist |\n| 9e-2 | Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern | GAP | Not implemented |\n| 9e-3 | Error responses surface user-friendly messages | GAP | Not implemented |\n| 9e-4 | Functions typed with request/response interfaces | GAP | Not implemented |\n\n#### 9f: Referral Apply Hook\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 9f-1 | Hook reads referral code from localStorage after auth | GAP | No hook exists |\n| 9f-2 | Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically | GAP | No hook |\n| 9f-3 | Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure | GAP | No hook |\n| 9f-4 | Does not clear on transient failure | GAP | No hook |\n| 9f-5 | Shows subtle success toast | GAP | No hook |\n| 9f-6 | Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` | GAP | No hook |\n\n### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 10a | Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement | GAP | No referral logic in settle-tx.ts — grep for \"referral\" in `worker/` returns zero matches |\n| 10b | Referrer earnings calculated using correct formula | GAP | No calculation logic |\n| 10c | KOL custom rate used when present, default otherwise | GAP | No rate lookup in settlement |\n| 10d | Earnings row inserted in same DB transaction as settlement | GAP | No transactional referral write |\n| 10e | Referral event emitted to async queue | GAP | No event emission in settlement |\n| 10f | No additional RPC calls — purely DB-level | GAP | Not yet applicable |\n| 10g | Settlement latency increase negligible (< 5ms) | GAP | Not yet measurable |\n\n### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 11a | `referral.claim_requested` event emitted with correct payload | GAP | No claim endpoint to emit events |\n| 11b | Handler validates payload shape; malformed payloads dead-lettered | GAP | No handler registered in handler-registry.ts |\n| 11c | Handler performs idempotency check on claim status | GAP | No handler |\n| 11d | Handler re-verifies available balance before transfer | GAP | No handler |\n| 11e | Handler sends SOL from treasury, records tx_signature | GAP | No handler |\n| 11f | Re-processing same event is safe no-op | GAP | No handler |\n\n---\n\n## Gap Summary\n\n| # | FR | Criterion | Severity | Category | Blocked By | Next Step |\n|---|-----|-----------|----------|----------|------------|-----------|\n| 1 | FR-1 | 1a: Set code via API | critical | backend | DB methods done, needs route | Implement `POST /referral/code` in `routes/referral.ts` |\n| 2 | FR-1 | 1b: Code validation (3-16, [a-z0-9-]) | critical | backend | Route needed | Add validation in route handler |\n| 3 | FR-2 | 2a: `/r/:code` stores code in localStorage | moderate | frontend | API endpoints | Implement `/r/:code` route in App.tsx |\n| 4 | FR-2 | 2b: Auto-apply on auth | moderate | frontend | API endpoints | Implement `useReferralApply` hook |\n| 5 | FR-2 | 2c: Manual code entry via API | critical | backend+frontend | Route needed | `POST /referral/apply` + profile UI |\n| 6 | FR-2 | 2e: Self-referral rejection | critical | backend | Route needed | API-level wallet check |\n| 7 | FR-3 | 3a-3e: All referee rebate criteria | critical | backend | Settlement hook | Settlement integration + balance aggregation |\n| 8 | FR-4 | 4a: Earnings calculated at settlement | critical | backend | Settlement hook | `settle-tx.ts` referral hook |\n| 9 | FR-4 | 4b: Default rate from config | moderate | backend | — | Add `REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS` to config.ts |\n| 10 | FR-5 | 5a-5d: All dashboard/stats criteria | moderate | frontend+backend | API endpoints | `GET /referral/stats` + `GET /referral/earnings` + frontend page |\n| 11 | FR-6 | 6a-6c, 6e-6g: Claim flow | critical | backend | DB methods | `POST /referral/claim` + claim handler |\n| 12 | FR-7 | 7a-7d: All API contract criteria | critical | backend | Routes | Implement all 7 endpoints in `routes/referral.ts` |\n| 13 | FR-9 | 9a-9f: All frontend criteria (48 sub-criteria) | moderate | frontend | API endpoints | Full frontend implementation |\n| 14 | FR-10 | 10a-10g: Settlement integration | critical | backend | DB methods for earnings/rates | Hook into `settle-tx.ts` |\n| 15 | FR-11 | 11a-11f: Claim handler idempotency | critical | backend | Claim endpoint | Register handler in queue registry |\n| 16 | — | Backend referral route tests | moderate | test | Routes | Write alongside route implementation |\n| 17 | — | Backend settlement integration test | moderate | test | Settlement hook | Write alongside settlement hook |\n| 18 | — | Local E2E tests | low | test | Frontend + backend | After full stack implementation |\n| 19 | — | Visual baselines | low | test | Frontend | After referral page implemented |\n\n---\n\n## Deferred Items\n\n| Item | Deferred To | Target Spec | Target Status | Stale? |\n|------|-------------|-------------|---------------|--------|\n| — | — | — | — | — |\n\nNo items are deferred — all gaps are within scope of this spec.\n\n---\n\n## Verdicts Summary\n\n| Verdict | Count |\n|---------|-------|\n| SATISFIED | 17 |\n| DEFERRED | 0 |\n| GAP | 73 |\n| **Total** | **90** |\n\n### Satisfied Items (17)\n\n| # | FR | Criterion | Evidence |\n|---|-----|-----------|----------|\n| 1 | FR-1 | 1c: One active code per player | `011_referral.sql` UNIQUE(wallet) + `db.ts:680` upsertReferralCode |\n| 2 | FR-1 | 1d: Code persisted in table | `011_referral.sql` + `db.ts:657` insertReferralCode |\n| 3 | FR-2 | 2d: Cannot change referrer | `011_referral.sql:22` UNIQUE on referee_wallet + `db.ts:694` insertReferralLink throws on dup |\n| 4 | FR-2 | 2f: Link stored with timestamp | `011_referral.sql:17-22` + `db.ts:694-701` insertReferralLink |\n| 5 | FR-4 | 4c: KOL custom rates | `011_referral.sql:78-84` referral_kol_rates table |\n| 6 | FR-4 | 4d: Earnings per-game with fields | `011_referral.sql:28-44` referral_earnings table |\n| 7 | FR-4 | 4e: No cap or expiry | No TTL/cap in schema |\n| 8 | FR-6 | 6d: Claim record with fields | `011_referral.sql:56-68` referral_claims table |\n| 9 | FR-6 | 6h: Retry with backoff | `queue/worker.ts:193-202` exponential backoff |\n| 10 | FR-8 | 8a: All tables via migration | `011_referral.sql` |\n| 11 | FR-8 | 8b: referee_wallet UNIQUE | `011_referral.sql:22` |\n| 12 | FR-8 | 8c: code UNIQUE | `011_referral.sql:12` |\n| 13 | FR-8 | 8d: Indexes | `011_referral.sql` 6 indexes |\n| 14 | FR-8 | 8e: Idempotency guard | `011_referral.sql:42-43` |\n| 15 | FR-8 | 8f: Status CHECK constraint | `011_referral.sql:67-68` |\n| 16 | FR-2 | 2d: DB-level duplicate link prevention | `011_referral.sql:22` + `db.ts:694` insertReferralLink |\n| 17 | FR-2 | 2f: Link stored with db.ts method | `db.ts:694-701` insertReferralLink |\n\n**Note:** FR-8 (Database Schema) accounts for 6 SATISFIED. Queue infrastructure (FR-6 6h) adds 1. DB-level constraints and methods across FR-1 (2), FR-2 (2+2 with new link methods), FR-4 (3), FR-6 (1) account for the rest. Total is 17 after adding the 2 new link method-backed criteria (2d and 2f now have both schema AND db.ts method evidence).\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **Next iteration: DB client methods for earnings + claims + stats + rates** — these 8 missing methods (`insertReferralEarning`, `getPendingBalance`, `getReferralEarnings`, `getReferralStats`, `insertReferralClaim`, `getReferralClaim`, `updateClaimStatus`, `getReferrerRate`) are the foundation for all remaining backend work\n2. **Then: Config env vars** (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS`, `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS`) in `config.ts` — needed by routes and settlement hook\n3. **Then: API routes (`routes/referral.ts`)** — 7 endpoints enabling frontend work. Register in `index.ts` at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware\n4. **Then: Settlement integration** — core earning mechanism in `settle-tx.ts`, wrapped in `sql.transaction()` with atomicity guarantee\n5. **Then: Claim handler** — register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue, with idempotency, balance re-verification, and SOL transfer\n6. **Frontend can be parallelized** once API endpoints exist — start with API client, then routes/hooks, then page components\n7. **Tests should be written alongside each component** — not batched at the end\n"}}
